Program: Outlook
Title: 30/08/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00x8gsg
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 31 Aug 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: Matthew Bannister meets Kazutaka Sato, the partner of a Japanese journalist Mika Yamamoto, who was shot dead in Syria. He describes how he discovered her body in an Aleppo hospital. Then, Outlook's Dorian Jones meets Kadriye Avci, a Turkish woman cleric who's campaigning for better conditions for female worshippers in Istanbul's mosques. And Melanie Burnett tells how she went from living rough on the streets of Amsterdam to getting her dream job. She is now about to become a law student. Show less